This paper deals with the calibration of a robotic system using sensor data, which is a core problem in robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also uses a stereo camera system, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper employs optimization techniques to calibrate the system, which is a common approach in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with the observability of the system, which is a key concept in control theory (cs.SY).
